                            <ns0:handNote><ns0:p>Small simple letters. Kappa has short equal arms, attached to the vertical; rho has small closed eye; mu has slanting first and final strokes, with the mid-strokes joining as a curve and only descending half-way; alpha is broad with straight bar, in one case slightly curved with the apex extending at the top; nu has shorter right vertical joining the diagonal above the line; omicron is small and mid-line.</ns0:p>
